column9: To be honest, support with girls. College has been so difficult because everyone is taken and you start to feel left out and don't really like to share personal things like that to people you don't trust. It would be nice to just have someone who pushes you to truly make good friends you can trust that doesn't involve RSO who only cares about the amount of people you can friend on Facebook, but something deeper than that..
column19: I've met amazing people outside of RSOs and this had always been true. RSOs celebrate a common interest, but this common interest isn't strong enough to keep a bond. Simply sharing a similar ethnic background race or origin would be a similarity, but sharing a personal experience and who you are through having introspection of another I believe actually creates a relationship. RSOs do celebrate culture in some sense which I think is fantastic to see, and again I'm not speaking in behalf of everybody.
